cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.SY 

The paper deals with distributed learning algorithms for achieving efficient correlated equilibria in game theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of a common random signal, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible sub-category. The paper also deals with multi-agent systems, which falls under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). Finally, the paper involves control and optimization, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
